  <text xml:lang="ta">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="MM1-intro">mutalāvatu viḻāvaṟaintapāṭṭu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">The first song, in which the [Indra] Festival is announced.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p type="edition"/>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="MM1">
<l>ulakan tiriyā vōṅkuyar viḻuccīrp</l>   
<l>palarpukaḻ mūtūrp paṇpu mēmpaṭīiya</l>   
<l>vōṅkuyar malayat taruntava ṉuraippat</l>   
<l>tūṅkeyi leṟinta toṭittōṭ cempiyaṉ</l>   
<l>viṇṇavar talaivaṉai vaṇaṅkimuṉ ṉiṉṟu</l>   
<l>maṇṇakat teṉṟaṉ vāṉpati taṉṉuṇ</l>   
<l>mēlōr viḻaiya viḻākkō ḷeṭutta</l>   
<l>nālēḻ nāḷiṉu naṉkiṉi tuṟaikeṉa</l>   
<l>vamarar talaiva ṉāṅkatu nērntatu</l>
<l>kavarāk kēḷviyōr kaṭavā rākaliṉ 	</l>
<l>meyttiṟam vaḻakku naṉporuḷ vīṭeṉu</l>
<l>mitiṟan tatta miyalpiṉiṟ kāṭṭuñ</l>
<l>camayak kaṇakkarun tantuṟai pōkiya</l>
<l>vamayak kaṇakkaru makalā rākik</l>
<l>karanturu veytiya kaṭavu ḷāḷarum</l>
<l>parantoruṅ kīṇṭiya pāṭai mākkaḷu</l>
<l>maimperuṅ kuḻuvu meṇpē rāyamum</l>
<l>vantoruṅku kuḻīi vāṉpati taṉṉuṭ</l>
<l>koṭittērt tāṉaik koṟṟavaṉ ṟuyaram</l>
<l>  viṭutta pūtam viḻākkōṇ maṟappiṉ 	</l>
<l>  maṭitta cevvāy valleyi ṟilaṅka</l>
<l>  viṭikkuraṉ muḻakkat tiṭumpai ceytiṭun</l>
<l>  toṭutta pācattut tolpati narakaraip</l>
<l>  puṭaittuṇum pūtamum poruntā tāyiṭu</l>
<l>  māyiru ñālat taracutalai yīṇṭu</l>
<l>  māyiraṅ kaṇṇōṉ viḻākkāl koḷkeṉa</l>
   
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <p>1.1-9 (9 lines) The Aetiology of the Indra Festival: The Cōḻa King Cempiyaṉ, on the command of the sage Akattiyaṉ, requests Lord Indra to come to stay in the Cōḻa city of Kāvirippūmpaṭṭiṉam for the 28 days of the Indra festival. Lord Indra consents. </p>
<l corresp="3">          When the man of rare penance (the sage Akattiyaṉ) commanded it [from his seat on] towering Mount Potiyam— </l>
<l corresp="2bc">          in order that the qualities of the ancient city (Kāvirippūmpaṭṭiṉam) </l>
<l corresp="1-2a">          extolled by many people [and] of sublime, towering fame/beauty/superiority/prosperity unchanging [in the eyes] of the world</l>
<l corresp="2d">          become [even more] widely known – </l>
<l corresp="4">          Cempiyaṉ (a Cōḻa king) of the shoulder-bangles, who destroyed the hanging fortresses,</l>
<l corresp="5">          standing bowed before the Lord of the Celestials (Indra), addressed [him]: </l>
<l corresp="6ab">          'May he who is [well] spoken of on earth (Indra) </l>
<l corresp="6cd, 8">          dwell very sweetly in the/his heavenly city (Kāvirippūmpaṭṭiṉam) for the twenty-eight days </l>
<l corresp="7">          during which the festival is held—since those on high (i.e. the gods) desire [it]!'</l>
<l corresp="9">          Thereupon the Lord of the Immortals (Indra) consented to that [request].  </l>
          
           

        </lg>
      </div>
